===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{m|enm|boot}}, {{m|enm|bot}}, {{m|enm|boet}}, {{m|enm|boyt||boat}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{m|ang|bāt||boat}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*baitaz}}, {{m|gem-pro|*baitą||boat, small ship}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{m|ine-pro|*bʰeyd-||to break, split}}. Cognate with {{cog|non|beit||boat}}, Middle Dutch {{m|dum|beitel||little boat}}.

{{cog|non|bátr|bátr}} (whence {{cog|is|bátur}}, {{cog|no|båt}}), {{cog|nl|boot}}, {{cog|de|Boot}}, {{cog|oc|batèl}} and {{cog|fr|bateau}} are all ultimately borrowings from the {{etyl|ang|-}} word.

